name: History of Computing
description: With this topic you'll learn about the history of computing and some of the most important events that shaped the Information Age.

name: Hardware
description: With this topic you will learn about the essential computer components and the different roles they play.

name: Operating Systems
description: With this topic you will learn about the underlying software that coordinates the different components of a computer.

name: Runtimes
description: With this topic you will learn about the process of turning human-readable code into commands that the computer can understand.

name: Spectrum of Platforms
description: With this topic you will learn about the different combinations of hardware operating systems and runtimes used to run software applications.

name: Types of Data
description: With this topic you'll learn about the spectrum of unstructured to structured data types and how to classify data correctly.

name: Data Storage
description: With this topic you'll learn techniques to store data of all types for usage in an application.

name: Data Manipulation
description: With this topic you'll learn how to interact with and manipulate data from storage providers using techniques such as SQL or SSH.

name: Data Wrangling
description: With this topic you'll learn to convert data from one type to another using data wrangling techniques.

name: Managing State
description: With this topic you'll learn about effectively using different patterns to manage the state in an application.
